main event: Witnessed a sighting of multiple unidentified objects over Georgetown, Massachusetts in February 1956.
interesting points: The observation lasted between 10 to 15 minutes., The objects initially moved toward the northeast before turning and moving away to the west., The sighting was reported by George and Frank Scully., The report included comments on the psychological manifestations in reporting objects., The investigation concluded the report was unreliable and suggested the objects could possibly be balloons.
